## 2. Search Intent & Target Audience

The primary searcher is a **prospective renter** in the middle of a housing search — likely in a coastal metro market — who has encountered the Avalon brand name through a listing site (Zillow, Apartments.com) or word-of-mouth and wants to verify what the brand represents before scheduling a tour or submitting an application. A secondary audience includes **current Avalon residents** researching other properties within the AvalonBay family (relevant to the Relocation Advantage program) and **investors or real estate professionals** monitoring AvalonBay's portfolio. The searcher is in the **consideration stage**, not pure discovery — they're not asking "what is an apartment," they're asking "is Avalon specifically right for me and worth the price." They expect a **hybrid format**: a quick definitional answer (what Avalon is), followed by a comparative breakdown (brands, price tiers, markets) and a practical evaluation guide (what to watch out for).

